      • initChannel

        public static void initChannel(android.content.Context context,
                               java.lang.String channel_id,
                               java.lang.String name,
                               java.lang.String description,
                               int importance)
        Creates a NotificationChannel with the given channel_id, name, description and importance. No action will be taken if Build.VERSION#SDK_INT is lower than 26.
        Parameters:
        context - the Context in which Context.getSystemService(String) will be called.
        channel_id - the id of the channel
        name - the name of the channel
        description - the description of the channel
        importance - the importance of the channel
        See Also:
        NotificationChannel.NotificationChannel(String, CharSequence, int)

                                                         java.lang.String channelId)
        Builds a notification with the given parameters.
        Parameters:
        context - the context used to create the notification.
        intent - the intent of the notification.
        title - the title of the notification.
        text - the text of the notification.
        icon - the icon of the notification.
        channelId - the id of the channel in which to publish the notification.
